<Class name="CM_ForkLiftStack" id="20e54e7e-8e1a-4a71-ba58-d7b9c77a6687">
    <superclass name="CM_GridArea"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>Is responsible for looking after the Fork Lift Stack areas defined in the system.
Looks after its graphical representation.
Rows, CM_YardLCArray, and location controllers are all created from the block definition at definition time.
A Row is bound to the first and last location controller in each row at definition time
The location dictionary is then populated by iterating over each row and related
location controllers.
CM_RestrictionSet apply at this level.</text>
